Examples from BEV:

1) The writer, proficient in BEV (as well as Academese), is remembering a past event...

"[He] finally come right out and ask for [it]...
...She too young."  

Minus the modifiers, a typical academese interpretation of the sentence might be:
*He come and ask
A plausible Academese revision:
He asked for it.

A gloss that takes into account some features of BEV tense marking:
He came right out and asked for it.

This leaves the two verbs sounding much less awkward, but why are there two?  Why not:
He boldly asked for it.  


